flow.mentorSays:
Perfect! Here's the optimal solution approach:

```typescript
app.get('/items', (req, res) => {
  const items = Array(100).fill(null).map((_, i) => ({ id: i + 1, name: `Item ${i + 1}` }));

  const page = parseInt(req.query.page) || 1;
  const limit = parseInt(req.query.limit) || 10;

  const startIndex = (page - 1) * limit;
  const endIndex = startIndex + limit;

  const paginatedItems = items.slice(startIndex, endIndex);

  res.json({
    data: paginatedItems,
    page,
    limit,
    total: items.length,
    totalPages: Math.ceil(items.length / limit)
  });
});
```

This solution demonstrates best practices for Nodejs development and shows how to properly implement Array slicing, query params.

